The following companies may have
significant price changes in  Hong Kong  trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses. Share prices are as of the last close.  The  Hang Seng Index  advanced 1.3 percent to 23,121.06. The
Hang Seng  China  Enterprises Index, which tracks so-called H
shares of Chinese companies, gained 2.6 percent to 12,398.05.  China Southern Airlines Co. (1055 HK): The carrier said it
aims to double flights servicing the southwestern Chinese region
of Guangxi in the next five years. The stock surged 6.5 percent
to HK$4.09.  Orange Sky Golden Harvest Entertainment (Holdings) Ltd.
(1132 HK): The film studio that made Bruce Lee famous delayed a
planned sale of yuan bonds in Hong Kong, according to a person
familiar with the matter. The stock slid 1.8 percent to 54 Hong
Kong cents.  PICC Property and Casualty Co. (2328 HK): Chinaâ€™s biggest
non-life insurer said direct premium income in January was 18.3
billion yuan ($2.77 billion). The stock climbed 2.6 percent to
HK$9.72.    ZTE Corp . (763 HK): The company plans to introduce open-
platform smartphones this year, Executive Vice President He Shiyou said. ZTE, a Chinese communications-equipment maker,
gained 1.5 percent to HK$30.70.  To contact the reporter on this story:
